## Complications of Pregnancy and Fertility
### Suzy Voters From Different Parties

#### By KATI ZERNERI

In the decades that Roe v. Wade was the law of the land, abortion rights groups tried to alter what support for it by declaring “Abortion Is Health Care.”

Only now, two years after the Supreme Court eliminated the constitutional right to abortion, and just six months before the presidential election, has the nation taken on the force of reality.

The public conversation about abortion has grown into one about the complexities of pregnancy and reproduction, as the consequences of bans have played out in the news. The question is no longer just whether you can get an abortion, but also if you can get it by pregnancy complications put you in jeopardy.
